comments.body: It was close to done shedding its skin when I ran into it. Close call; glad he/she was slow moving.
Maybe — although, it does almost look like an underbite of a Nerodia...  @gtsalmon and @wild-about-texas have helped me out a bunch with these in TX.

identifications.body:
Definitely a Nerodia... although opaque, the round pupil is clearly discernible and, while faint, the bars on the lips are visible. Given the placement of the eyes on the head, I am comfortable iding this as N. erythrogaster rather than N rhombifer...
@gtsalmon
